%N A098082 Absolute values of elements of flattened successive matrices B(k), k>=0, read by rows where B(k) = M^k*C where M=[[-1, 1, 0], [0, -1, 1], [1, 1, -1]] and C = [[0, 1, 1], [1, 1, 1], [1, 1, 2]].
%C A098082 Minimal Pisot generator matrix minus identity 3 X 3 Markov sequence.
%C A098082 The minimal Pisot generator matrix M has identity: M^3-M-I=0 which suggests the binomial forms as Markov's: (M+I)^n = M^(3*n) (M-1)^n = Sum_{m=0..n} (-1)^m*C(n,m)*M^(n-m).
%C A098082 There seems to be a near matrix ring type behavior of these matrices with I.
%t A098082 Clear[x, M, A] digits=21 M={{0, 1, 0}, {0, 0, 1}, {1, 1, 0}} M0=M-IdentityMatrix[3] Det[M0] A[n_]:=M0.A[n-1]; A[0]:={{0, 1, 1}, {1, 1, 1}, {1, 1, 2}}; (* flattened sequence of 3 X 3 matrices made with an alternating recurrence*) b=Flatten[Table[Abs[A[n]], {n, 0, digits}]] ListPlot[b, PlotJoined->True]
